Subject: Mesa Problem and a solution
From: Thomas Frieden <ThomasF@hyperion-software.de>
Date: Mon, 9 Apr 2001 23:17:37 +0200

Hi,

Here's a solution for the Mesa slowdowns:
setenv Warp3D/ForceVersion 3

This will bring skyfly back to 27 fps.

The effect of this variable is that the main library now assumes that the 
driver library is a V3 library and will not call new functions (it will 
emulate the remaining stuff, like the vertex arrays).

For Shogo, I would advice to remove the variable to make use of the added 
speed of the real vertex arrays (Shogo only uses vertex arrays except for 
very few operations).

I *suspect* the problem with V4 and Mesa to be related to the amount of state 
changes. I'll keep you informed...

Regards,
