Hi,

On Sunday 08 April 2001 16:37, DJNick wrote:
> One question: why in GLQuake quick saving & loading works much faster than
> on Heretic2 and now Shogo?

Because both Heretic and Shogo use much more data for that...

When you save a game (no matter what), the games saves it's internal state, 
which is the current state of everything in the level, like doors, enemies, 
ammo boxes. Shogo is object oriented, which means every entity in the game is 
a C++ object (the source code for the game logic is available, so you can 
have a look if you're interested). When saving a game, every object is asked 
to save it's internal state. Shogo has a lot more objects to care for than 
Quake....

Regards,
-- 
