Well, I think it's better to actually reduce the overhead of the state 
changes in Warp3D. V4 now checks back with the hardware driver everytime the 
program does a W3D_SetState (This is critical for the Voodoo driver, as a 
state change may affect a lot of registers on the Voodoo).
