I don't think it will go noticeably faster...

> Ok, it works great. Should I disable this "VFAST" now (set to "0"?) to make
> Shogo run normal or this command won't cause slowdown on MiniGL games? I
> haven't tried yet, but your word is final :)

VFAST is mesa-exclusive, it doesn't have anything to do with MiniGL. For 
optimal performance on Shogo, you have to delete 'ForceVersion' again. 

> One more thing: In Env:Warp3D I have following dirs and files:
>
> Permedia2                          Dir ----rwed 07-Apr-01 14:19:24
> CyberGFX                           Dir ----rwed 07-Apr-01 14:18:06
> Virge                              Dir ----rwed 07-Apr-01 14:18:06
> ForceVersion                         1 ----rw-d Today     18:59:54
> QUEUESIZE                            4 ----rw-d 07-Apr-01 14:18:06
>
> Do I need "VIRGE" dir? What will happen if I delete it? What is QUEUESIZE
> for? (it is set to 8192). Do I need something more?

Virge is not needed, in fact you only need the directory that corresponds to 
your graphics system (CyberGfx in this case) and your graphics card 
(Permedia2). 

QUEUESIZE is from a deprecated feature called "Indirect Mode". This mode was 
used in an older Port of Mesa, but was dropped later because performance 
wasn't good with it. It needs not be present, since a resonable default is 
assumed within Warp3D...

