The problem with these is that they patch system functions. Now every time 
you use a system function you assume a certain behaviour. Birdie for example 
patches cybergraphics and intuition, and may interfere with the way that 
bitmaps are used in Warp3D for texture storage. The whole bitmap handling is 
a hack anyway, because it is misused for video memory allocation that is not 
there.

> ONLY 50 FPS ?
>
> When the driver will be complete, I assume it will be 150
> FPS ! :-)

No. ADescent syncs to the screen refresh... In 800x600 it gets problematic 
anyway because the CPU and graphics chip draw stuff at the same time... This 
would need an overhaul, if I had the time...

> What are the best variables values for DescentW3D ?

All the default values are mentioned in the W3D doc files. There shouldn't be 
any special stuff required. 

The only thing that I can think of right now it that your Stack might be set 
too low. What are you using?

You might also want to try a completely clean boot with nothing else in it... 

