Generally, I have to say that I am missing the time to do it (same goes for 
Peter I guess). I had thought about a few additions in the past - they would 
be relatively easy to do. I was thinking about smoke trails for the missiles, 
and lens flares for explosions, and most of all moving all drawing operations 
to the 3D hardware. 

The reason explosions look blocky is because they are drawn with the CPU. 
Since Descent was never done with 3DHW in mind, the explosion bitmaps where 
not the right size (i.e. a power of two), so using them as a texture was not 
really easy. OK, it is easy, but it requires using a larger texture and using 
just parts of it...

However, the first version was done on the ViRGE. On my A2000, the ViRGE only 
had 3.5 megs of memory, and that means that only 0.5 (!) megs of texture 
memory was available. It was next to impossible to get all the textures for 
the walls in there, and there was definately no room for anything else...

MouseInvert should be in there IIRC, you should be able to invert every axis 
individually...

